  m_text: Red Foxes are well-known for their role in Finnish culture, particularly
    in folklore regarding the Northern Lights. Finnish mythology features a magical
    firefox (Tulikettu), which was believed to be a rare creature whose fur created
    sparks when it brushed against snow, causing the Northern Lights.
